- Apply side effects to components[Fetching data to setting up intervals]
- Runs function on component reload
- By default, runs on every reload or specify to run only when certain values change.
- When empty array given, it will run only on mount[componentDidMount alternative]
- Adding and removing DOM listeners

import React, {useEffect} from 'react';
React.useEffect(()=>{},[])




useEffect(()=>{
 return ()=>{
     if(timeout){
         clearTimeout(timeout);
     }
 }
},[])

useEffect(()=>{
 return ()=>{
     if(timeout){
         clearTimeout(timeout);
     }
 }
},[time, setTime])

useEffect(()=>{
 return ()=>{
     if(timeout){
         clearTimeout(timeout);
     }
 }
})


useEffect(()=>{
    window.addEventListener("scroll", scrollHandler)
 return ()=>{
      window.removeEventListener("scroll", scrollHandler)
 }
},[])



Note: Write async function outside and call it from inside the useEffect